<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-07-17T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-07-17T12:00:00-05:00" n="628" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.6363 Barco/109: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Piles</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-17T12:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">July 17,
                                        1928—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 10
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>58. I consider the situation to be as set forth by the Department in its
                            37, July 16, 12 noon.</p>
                        <p>It is my opinion that the Government will take no action thereon unless
                            pressed. The Foreign Minister is ill. I am trying to see the President
                            and will cable immediately thereafter.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Piles</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>